&lt;p&gt;Tissue Viability Specialist Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a registered nurse who has a passion for wound care to join a small but highly motivated Tissue viability team within an integrated Trust which includes community and hospital setting. The Tissue viability team aim to promote the delivery of high quality, patient focused evidence based practice. The team objectives are aligned to national and local agreed quality agendas and the promotion of safe harm free care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit an individual who has relevant knowledge, skills and experience in all aspects of wound care including pressure ulcer management and prevention, complex wound management and leg ulcer management. A key element of the role is the provision of education, training and support to members of the MDT, therefore teaching experience is desirable. The successful candidate will play a pivotal role in providing evidence based training and care in all aspects of tissue viability and complex wound management. The individual should have excellent communication and organisational skills, be able to work automatously and work as part of a dedicated team of Tissue Viability nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role allows opportunity for working in both Hospital and Community settings.&lt;/p&gt;
